  <Subject Subject_ID="300264909">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300024659</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>equipment by process [300024659], equipment [300122241], Tools and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300022238], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Generally, devices that can transform an input of physical quantity, usually coming from an energy source, into an output quantity typically of a different kind, for instance, converting solar heat into electricity, or pressure into hydraulic energy. Many devices, such as phonograph pickups, microphones, thermometers, loudspeakers, and light meters, can be termed transducers. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In het algemeen apparaten die een ingevoerde fysieke hoeveelheid, meestal afkomstig uit een energiebron, kunnen omzetten in een andersoortige hoeveelheid uitvoer, bijvoorbeeld zonnewarmte in elektriciteit of druk in hydraulische energie. Veel apparaten, zoals grammofoons, thermometers, luidsprekers en lichtmeters, kunnen worden betiteld als transducers.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052403/Van Dale Groot Woordenboek (1998)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一般而言，指可以將通常是能量來源的輸入物理量轉換、輸出為不同種類物理量的裝置，像是將太陽熱能轉換為電力，或壓力轉換為水力能。諸如留聲機拾音器、麥克風、溫度計、擴聲器、電表等裝置均可稱換能器。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
